# Automation scripts (token-aware)

**Prefer existing scripts over ad-hoc commands** when it saves tokens or time.

| When | Script | Example |
|------|--------|--------|
| Full gate (lint + tests) | `.\scripts\check-all.ps1` | Before commit/PR |
| Quick iterations (tests only) | `.\scripts\check-all.ps1 -SkipPreCommit` | After code change |
| Lint/format only (no pytest) | `.\scripts\lint-only.ps1` | After docs/templates/style change |
| Subset of tests | `.\scripts\quick-test.ps1 -Path tests/test_foo.py` or `-Keyword "content_type"` | When iterating on one area |

Avoid raw `pytest`/`ruff` invocations when a script covers the need; scripts keep behaviour consistent and reduce back-and-forth. See `.cursor/skills/token-aware-automation/SKILL.md` for when to use which.

